post_text: May ISD will have Flu Vaccines at May First Baptist Church on 9/23/20 from 8 am to 10 am. United Pharmacy will be here to administer them. If you have Insurance, Medicare, or Medicaid, they will file for you. If you would like your child vaccinated, you can send a flu form and a copy of insurance card with them to school. The price for the shot without insurance is $37. The public is welcome to come get their Flu vaccine also. Any questions please call Rachel Beal at 254-259-3711.

We will be pre-selling tickets for the September 4 - May vs Sterling City Football Game:

Monday-Tuesday (8/31-9/1): Pre-sale will begin at 8:30 AM for parents of Football Players, Band Members, and Cheerleaders

Wednesday-Friday (9/2-9/4): remaining tickets will be sold to the general public.

There will be a limit of 2 tickets per family and 300 tickets will be sold.

Tickets will be available in the Administration Office and are $5 for adults and $3 for students. Please bring exact change.

The final shopping for items that needed to be added to the list was completed this weekend. Thank you to everyone that volunteers to make our PTO awesome!

Mid-summer the PTO sent out over 200 letters to local businesses and churches in Brown county. Out of those letters we have received a response from 11.

There will be more news in the near future, our district is truly blessed.

post_text:
Just a reminder that school starts on Monday! Our district is working hard to make this year as normal as possible for our Tigers! Please remember there are a couple of new state requirements that we have to abide by during Covid: students will need to wear asks (please put your child's name on it) and parents will not be allowed to walk your student to their classrooms the first day. Visitors will not be allowed past the office.

This is a very trying time for everyone, but we thankful we get to go back to school! We are ready to see our kids, and we are ready for a GREAT school year. Together, we will make the best of this!

post_text:
From our band director, Mr. Flenniken: I'm always proud of our band no matter what- but today my amazement at these young musicians has risen to yet new and unfathomable heights!

We set out to Hamilton with tons of rain and wind- arrived to discover the contest was running behind schedule.... but the band stayed focused and played better than I think we have EVER played at a contest before, and we emerged with the coveted FIRST DIVISION rating in both Concert and Sightreading!!

I'm not one to care about a trophy count or always getting 1st place- but what I "do" care about is seeing the smiles and joy on my student's faces when we put in the hard work and effort- and it is recognized by the judges!!

Band- thank you for all your dedication and hard work- it is such a pleasure to get to work with you and share in your successes.... now for a well deserved break!! Go Band!!

post_text: The May High School robotics team, known as ‚Äú4cbb17‚Äù, has been participating in the Waco League of the FIRST Tech Challenge robotics tournaments since November 2019. Our team was the only 1-A public school in the league, comprised of teams from 6-A school districts, 4-A Charter Schools, GWAMA (a high tech magnet school), and private schools. During the Championship held Saturday, Jan. 25, 2020, team 4cbb17 was invited to participate in the semi-finals as the alliance partner with the ‚ÄúChicken Gang Robotics" from Midway High School. The Alliance lost the last of 2 out of 3 games by a close margin, missing the opportunity to progress to the Regional tournament. We did earn the Pit Award! We are proud of this growing program! Congratulations!

post_text: Congratulations, girls!! State Bound!!
shared_text:
Brownwood Bulletin
October 28, 2019 at 4:26 PM ¬∑

May Lady Tigers freshman Jazmyn Rainey and junior Melanie Murphree have qualified for the UIL Class A girls cross country state meet. At the Region III-A meet in Dallas, Rainey (12:55.78) placed fifth overall and second among the top 10 individuals not on one of the four advancing teams, while Murphree (13:27.11) was 18th overall and 9th among the top 10. State is Nov. 9 in Round Rock.

post_text:
Flu Vaccines: The Health Dept. will be at May ISD on 10/8/19 for flu vaccines. If your child has medicaid, it will cover the vaccine. Send back the form with a copy of the card. If he/she has Chips insurance, send a copy of the card with the co-pay amount. If the child does not have insurance, the cost will be $14.00 and with insurance the cost will be $25.00.

United Pharmacy will be here on 10/9/19. If the student has insurance, they will file the insurance. The student has to be at least 7 years old. If parents or community members would like a flu vaccine, they are available on both days from 8-10 am.

JH and HS student can pick up a vaccine form in the HS office, and forms were sent home with all elementary students in their green folders.

If you have any questions, please call Rachel Beal, our school nurse, at 254-259-3711 or contact her by email at rachel.beal@mayisd.com.

ATTENTION:

FFA Parent Meeting Tuesday, August 27th at 6:00 p.m. in the Ag Classroom. If your child is planning to participate in any aspect of FFA this year, they along with a parent or guardian need to attend the meeting tomorrow night. We will be discussing new opportunities, exploring interests, and signing up for both junior and senior FFA. If your kiddo plans to participate in an CDE, LDE, or exhibition events under May FFA they MUST BE A CURRENT MEMBER. Remember, FFA is so much more than just cows and plows!

Please share and help us get the word out!

It‚Äôs that time of year again, stock show season is quickly approaching. With that being said, we want to ensure that everyone who exhibits animals via May FFA at the Texas Major Livestock Shows gets their state validation tags ordered. Please let our new Ag teacher (her information can be found below) know how many tags you need and for what species by Friday August 23rd before 1:00 p.m.

If you are considering or wanting to know more about participating in FFA or showing livestock this year please contact her soon so she can help you stay ahead of deadlines.

We look forward to a great year growing our Ag program! Swing by the Ag shop and meet Ms. Perkins during open house next week!

Codi Perkins
codi.perkins@mayisd.com
(325) 200-1898

Youth football and cheer and parents!! Please mark your calendars for Monday, July 8.

Football will meet in the library, and cheer will meet in the foyer of the new gym.

5:30-Cheer fitting for K-6th grade.

5:30 - Football uniform fittings and registration for all 5/6 PLAYERS. Players need to be present.

6:15 - Meeting for parents of players KINDERGARTEN THROUGH 6th GRADE. Flag (K-2) registration at this time. (Flag players are welcome, but do not have to attend.)

6:30 - Uniform fittings and registration for all 3/4 PLAYERS. Players need to be present.

All parents must fill out registration forms and attend the meeting. If you are unable to make it, please notify Tiffany Baker @ 325-642-5514 BEFORE the meeting to make arrangements to get your registration completed. In order to ensure equipment/uniforms for all players, the last day to register for the season is July 8. The $75 payment per player is due on or before August 6. Please share and let us know if you have any questions. Go TIGERS!!
